highlights.description: Description of NYPL partnership with LVN.
Participants validate Carole's feelings when she felt it wasn't right that she was asked to get out of a seat reserved for elderly when she is over 80 years old.
Shared experiences with people with backpacks not paying attention to it hitting someone on the bus or train.
Bridgette shares her own opinion to reinforce another participant's point.
Participant attended all six conversations held by this library branch.

title: Lower East Side Conversation - Transportation and Seniors
